text: Por or POR may refer to: ==Por== *Por (Thai word) *Por, Armenia, a town * Por, a Spanish preposition * Por, a Portuguese preposition ==POR== * POR (gene), cytochrome P450 reductase * Power-on reset * Profit (accounting) on return * Program of Record (PoR), a US funded Acquisition Program usually of the US military or NASA; see Glossary of military modeling and simulation ==Politics== * Partido Obrero Revolucionario (disambiguation), commonly referred to by the Spanish initials POR * Party of the Right (disambiguation), any of several organizations ==Places== * Portugal (FIFA and IOC trigrams) * Portland Transportation Center, United States; Amtrak station code POR * Common abbreviation for the U.S. city of Portland, Oregon * Pori Airport, Finland; IATA airport code POR * Porth railway station, Wales; National Rail station code POR ==See also== *Poor (disambiguation) *Pore (disambiguation)
